      <div type="description" n="monument">
        <head>Description of Monument</head>
        <p>A <rs type="material" key="marmor">white marble</rs> <rs type="objectType">lintel</rs> block, broken in two (<measure type="length" unit="metre" dim="height">0.15</measure> ×
<measure type="length" unit="metre" dim="width">c. 1.15</measure> × <measure type="length" unit="metre" dim="depth">0.455</measure>) over the entrance to a tomb chamber. A
second chamber was subsequently constructed at right angles to the
first, and the lintel over its entrance abuts on to our inscription,
partially obscuring the right end.</p>
      </div>

      <div type="description" n="text">
        <head>Description of Text</head>
        <p><rs type="execution" key="scalpro">Inscribed</rs> along the face.</p>
      </div>

      <div type="description" n="letters">
        <head>Description of Letters</head>
        <p>The angular letters are similar to those of <xref type="inscription" n="165" href="130113">13.113</xref>; <measure type="length" unit="metre" dim="height">0.035</measure>. The <foreign lang="grc">Υ</foreign> at
the end of the name is <measure type="length" unit="metre" dim="height">0.045</measure>, and the one letter serves as the ending
of the two words in the genitive.</p>
      </div>

      <div type="description" n="date">
        <head>Date</head>
        <p><date exact="none" cert="low" notBefore="0401" notAfter="0500">Fifth century</date> or later.</p>
      </div>

      <div n="text" lang="grc" type="edition">
        <head lang="en">Edition</head>
        <ab>
		  	<lb n="1"/><w lemma="Α">Α</w> <g type="chi-rho"/> <w lemma="Ω">Ω</w> <persName key="theopropius1" type="aphrodisian" full="yes"><name reg="Θεοπρόπιος">Θεοπρο<unclear reason="damage">π</unclear><supplied reason="lost">ίο</supplied>υ</name></persName> <g type="leaf"/> <w lemma="Α">Α</w> <g type="chi-rho"/> <w lemma="Ω">Ω</w> <w lemma="ζάω"><hi rend="supraline">ζῇ</hi></w><lb n="2"/><rs type="official-relig" key="bishop"><w lemma="ἐπίσκοπος">ἐπισ<unclear reason="damage">κ</unclear><supplied reason="lost">όπο</supplied>υ</w></rs>.</ab>
      </div>

      <div type="translation">
        <head>Translation</head>
        <ab><supplied reason="subaudible">Tomb of</supplied> Theopropios, bishop. He lives.</ab>
      </div><div type="commentary">
        <head>Commentary</head>
        <p>See discussion at <xref type="eAla-text" n="IX.35">IX.35</xref>. For
Theopropios see also <xref type="inscription" n="165" href="130113">13.113</xref>.</p>
      </div>

      <div type="history" n="locations"><head>Locations</head><p><rs type="found"><rs type="monuList">Necropolis, North-east</rs>: in the Turkish cemetery (which lies over an
earlier cemetery).</rs>. <rs type="origLocation">Findspot</rs>. <rs type="lastLocation">Findspot.</rs>. </p></div>

      

      

